{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is at the boundary between manifest validation and module-loading/orchestration, not inside one pure function. A unit test of only schema validation could pass while the real loader still imports the plugin before rejecting it.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one plugin whose manifest omits a required field and whose entry module has a detectable side effect (e.g., writes a marker file or flips shared state on import). Run the real loader against the directory; assert rejection error is reported and the side effect never occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.28,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This requires real interaction among manifest parsing, dependency graph resolution, and hook invocation order across multiple plugin modules. Unit-testing topological sort alone misses orchestration bugs in actual loader execution.","test_description":"Set up two real plugin packages in a temp directory: A depends on B. Each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-process log/file. Run loader and assert observed order is [B, A].","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.16,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle detection must be verified in the real loader path that also controls whether hooks execute. A unit test of graph-cycle detection alone can miss a bug where cycle is detected but one plugin still loads.","test_description":"Create plugins A and B with mutual dependencies; each entry/onLoad records execution. Run loader and assert cycle error is reported and neither plugin entry nor `onLoad` runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Evidence: Behavior explicitly checks ordering between module import side effects and lifecycle hook invocation inside one loader run.\nLower-level miss-proof: A unit test on hook-caller logic cannot expose wrong sequencing with actual module import/execution timing.\nFinal label: Integration (no real network/subprocess/external API; no AI output dependency; single-step non-agentic flow).","test_description":"Build one plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.pluginInit = 'entry-executed'` during import, and whose `onLoad` asserts that value is already set, then records success. Run loader; test fails if `onLoad` runs before import side effect.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.61,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is multi-module orchestration: error isolation + dependency-aware continuation. Unit tests for try/catch or dependency checks independently can miss combined behavior in the loader pipeline.","test_description":"Create three plugins: F throws in `onLoad`; I is independent; D depends on F. Run loader and assert: F error is reported, I `onLoad` still runs, D does not run because dependency failed. Validate final loader status reflects partial initialization.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
